raw_data.description: A locally owned coffee shop in Charlotte, NC offering indoor/outdoor seating, to-go, and catering for private events.

reviews_data.review_text: Cute little shop, I truly loved the look of it. It was so cozy! Their “camp” menu was adorable and well thought out. The regular menu caught my eye too. I definitely want to come back to try more of their items.

Located in the lobby of this office building, this tiny coffee shop gets the job done. They have limited seating inside and out, but the hightop tables outside worked for me with a nearby power outlet.

I enjoyed my small latte very much and sitting here for two hours was easy. Parking on a nearby street was free. Just be sure not to block a fire hydrant or a driveway - the next car up from me had a parking ticket!

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Lovely little cafe overall. The baristas were very sweet. I had the rosemary honey latte and my husband had the banana pudding latte both 10/10
Such a cute little shop. Everyone is always so kind, great seasonal drinks, and they validate parking! We love going to wildroots!

Not impressed! They made the lattes looks so good and in glass glasses. We got plastic glasses and the banana whatever it was didn’t have anything in it. My daughter had the cinnamon latte and we both almost chocked on the amount of cinnamon. I wouldn’t ever go back. There are so many other coffee shops that show up!
My matcha was very good & sweet!

A nice chill environment and cute cubbies for selfies.  Had the chocolate chip cookie latte slightly customized to be less sweet, 1/2 sweetener. It had good flavor but was still very very sweet.  Even after adding a 3rd shot of espresso it was too sweet.  Friendly young ladies but overall customer service needs improvement. Observed 3 other orders go back up to have changes made to their drinks. No option to remake my drink, only to add the additional (3rd) shot of espresso to it.  With modifications to the ratios of ingredients used, this could be a wonderful latte. It was the most expensive latte I’ve ever ordered at any coffee shop.  Prices are a bit high.

Best place to get Matcha drinks in CLT.
We love our Matcha Lavender’s from here! And they make some awesome coffees with some great artwork as well.

i just had the chocolate chip cookie latte from the newest menu and it’s SO GOOD!!! the salted vanilla cold foam is the perfect balance of sweet and salty! the spring menu was incredible and the newest summer menu has a key lime pie latte, which is my FAVORITE! my fave place to get coffee and matcha! support local small business ❤️

The coffee here is genuinely so bad. The iced vanilla latte is decent but super watery. DO NOT get the chocolate chip cookie latte. It is SO insanely salty from the salted vanilla cold foam…would probably be fine without it but the espresso is watery nonetheless. The blueberry pancake latte is such a weird experience to drink..very tart and thin and just…bad. But the workers were very nice and provided great service! Good environment inside too. But the coffee is BAD
Such nice service, such a cute spot, delicious coffee (the cinnamon and honey was a must)! Would come back when visiting Charlotte!
so cute!! looks like my pinterest dreams! walls, counter, seating, even the glassware. small with limited seating. the maldon salted maple latte was delicious

This place is phenomenal! I flew into Charlotte for less than 24 hours for an event and looked up good coffee shops to go to before my event, and I am so glad I came here! The jams, the ambiance, the music, the staff, THE LATTE’S…everything is *chefs kiss* ! I had the iced latte with fruit loops and it was so good that I had to order another one before I left! The avocado toast was also phenomenal. Y’all are doing it, ladies! This is a must try! If i was in Charlotte, I’d definitely be a regular! I especially loved those sitting/reading nooks! It’s really a place you can catch up with friends, have a solo date, relax, catch up on work, or do anything! They have a space to sit for each mood!
I love the nostalgic vibe of this place.
I really like this place it has homemade syrups and the coffee is locally roasted.
We’ve lived in Charlotte for years and this is our favorite spot! Best lattes and seasonal flavors. Recently added food is also delicious! Hidden gem for sure.
Neat place. Latte and pastry were both great, as was the service! Would come in regularly if we lived in the area.
I’ve tried hot & iced options here and they’re all great. The flavored lattes are so smooth without being overly sweet or bitter. The seasonal options are fun!! Gingerbread is my favorite
One of my favorite places to get a latte. Definitely check out their seasonal options!!
Such a cute spot, I just wish it was bigger! Drink was good but very light on the flavors , mostly tasted like your choice in milk, so chose one you like the flavor of!
I love this place! The coffee is delicious! The homemade pop tarts are great too, just make sure you get there early before the sell out!

The customer service needs some improvement..maybe even a smile or even a warm friendly hello would be a good start. There were no options for anything to eat. Coffee was overpriced and bitter. The space is cute though.

Went morning of 6/2, the woman working was rude & nasty. Very poor customer service. The coffee was good but not enough to return. As someone who has worked in Customer Service all my life I was really disappointed that such a cute place had such a miserable person working.
Got the madon salted maple latte! 😋 Good vibes, good spots. Validated parking for the attached parking lot.

Specialty drinks: Delicious
Wi-Fi name and password: Both "wildroots"
Vibe/ambiance: Hippie
Parking: Parking garage visitor spots
Parking validation: 90 minutes
Seating: Limited. Three tables for two, two tables for four right outside of entrance to rest of complex. Additional two cubbyholes with beaded drapes.
Should you try this place? Yes.
Bathrooms: One all gender restroom.

Getting to the cafe is fairly easy and they validate parking. Loved the aesthetic, but didn't see any food options available at the time that I went. The barista was nice and I enjoyed my Lavender Vanilla Latte with almond milk. The cups the drinks were served in are so cute.
Though it has only the coffee menu and very limited other breakfast options, the Cafe’s minimalist charm and quality of coffee makes this a delight. Very peaceful space for focused work for a change.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: I love this coffee shop!  My husband and I stop by whenever we're nearby, and it's always super tasty and the baristas are nice.  Great decor and good vibes.  I love all of their lattes and iced coffees, we always recommend this place.

I want to like this coffee shop more than I do in reality. I stop by in the mornings some days because I work close and every time I have been, something has been missing: a drink I want is out, there’s no food, etc. Whatever I do get there is quality and tasty. The staff is always personable, but after three visits with missing things, I can’t ignore that. It’s also not the kind of coffee shop I would stay at for a long time meeting someone or working; it doesn’t have that comfortable vibe.
Love this coffee shop and love the owner. Great place and delicious coffee!

I love craft coffee and Wildroots has been continuously supplying some of the best coffee in CLT for years! The PSL is the best I’ve ever had! And if you are looking for something different, try the PSL Matcha!!
Very neat little spot. Coffee was great and the service friendly. Evergthing was ready very quickly. Would go back if in the area again.
Best coffee in Charlotte. We chose to sit down and enjoy our coffee and were able to choose from a variety of coffee cups to drink out of. Definitely coming back again
Two starts because the place is unbelievably cute! Unfortunately I didn’t make it 10 feet on the sidewalk before throwing away my latte. The quality of espresso was tragic
This coffee shop is super cute and had a great atmosphere. They have tables and these cute little cubby holes to relax in more private. The coffee was good and they have free wifi!

Undoubtedly, this coffee shop is a true hidden gem. Every flavor on their menu is exceptional, with my personal favorite being the Honey Cinnamon Latte. The owner and baristas create a friendly and welcoming atmosphere. Moreover, the shop’s adorable ambiance adds to the overall experience. An added convenience is that they validate your parking so you are able to enjoy your time there without any worries. For anyone seeking the best and most delightful coffee experience in Charlotte, Wildroots is the place to be.
The blackberry cobbler was as cool and refreshing as the vibe in this sixties seventies nostalgic lounge!

4.5! Very nice barista, and the drinks were good too. I preferred the Blackberry Cobbler latte to my girlfriend’s Strawberry Dream, but she enjoyed hers too. We didn’t get to have them in the adorable glasses which was unfortunate, but we’ll be back!

Just had the Honduran dark roast as a pour over and it was good. Just the fact that they know where the bean was from and what kind of roast it is means they have a passion for good coffee. Plus the barista is incredibly cute! I’ll be back!
Great coffee shop and immaculate retro vibes! Definitely worth stopping in for a lavender latte or cortado. They validate parking too!
This place is a vibe. The decor is 70's vintage and the coffee options are so flavorful and unique. Would 10/10 recommend to grab an iced or hot coffee from this place.
Very sweet people and great coffee! We loved the furniture, style, and atmosphere of the shop. Barista was kind and even gave us breakfast recommendations!

They have such yummy coffee and the owner and her team are so nice.  The customer service is amazing and the ambience is super chill and relaxing.  I always look forward to grabbing a coffee from here!

My husband and I love this place we always go right before 2pm everything about their coffee is perfect. We are Colombian so we know about quality coffee. Their Lavender syrup which is naturally made is top notch and the staff, owner and overall place is always on point and extremely nice! We are customers and we followed to the new location!
My latte was bitter and very overpriced.
Slow. 20 minutes for two coffees. I was the only customer in the shop
Awesome coffee!
Amazing coffee and a great atmosphere. Try the honey cinnamon. You won't regret it. This place is a whole vibe. Definitely making this a regular coffee spot to visit in Southend!

The coffee was very good but it was hard to even find the coffee shop because it’s hard to see from the outside and also having no bathroom isn’t cool at all for a place that literally sells something that’s a diuretic. A good place to just grab a coffee and go I guess.
Cool space but terribly pulled espresso and no restroom. How does a coffee shop not have a restroom?

It's a very cute and cozy coffee shop where I always feel welcomed. Baristas there would always greet me with a smile and would customize any drink to my liking. Great to have this option near work. The entrance is to the right of the Sweat Method. They close at 2:00 pm.

Extremely quaint and comfortable inside. Honey-cinnamon latte was delicious. Definitely a good little spot to grab a cup of coffee with friends.

Seating is a bit limited inside, but we had no problem getting a seat.

This place is wonderful. The coffee (and tea) are both perfectly made, each and every time. Walking in, the shop itself was so thoughtfully curated. Everything is so aesthetically pleasing! And don’t get me started on the owner, Jasmine, she’s so sweet. 100% would recomment!
Always a great visit. The oat milk iced cortado is so smooth, staff is friendly, and they serve local coffee!!!  Must try!
Iced oatmilk latte was good, but the highlight of my visit was the vegan blueberry lemon pop-tart! So delicious and not overly sweet👌🏼Cool area too.

What once was the cutest little coffee trailer is now the cutest little coffee shop in South End.

I had the salted Maldon maple latte with oat milk and it was delicious!

I give this place five stars, but if what the other reviewer said about no public restroom and no air conditioning is true, I would knock my rating down. (It was cold and rainy the day I went)
Wonderful coffee.  Wonderful owner.  Hard to beat it in Southend.

Probably great for a pick up and run but no public restroom, not sure if there's WiFi, it was 1,000 degrees inside and they still require masks even though the mandate has lifted. You won't want to bring your laptop in and work from here for more than 10 minutes. My iced latte was good, though 😐
One of the best coffee shops I’ve visited. Locally owned and an absolutely beautiful atmosphere!! Payment was easy and the espresso was NOT BURNT! YAY!!
Great options for flavored lattes!
Kind service and great hot chocolate with several milk options. Will be back!
Delish iced latte, cute interior, and good convo with the owner! Excited to go back.

reviews_data.review_text: I love this coffee shop!  My husband and I stop by whenever we're nearby, and it's always super tasty and the baristas are nice.  Great decor and good vibes.  I love all of their lattes and iced coffees, we always recommend this place.

I want to like this coffee shop more than I do in reality. I stop by in the mornings some days because I work close and every time I have been, something has been missing: a drink I want is out, there’s no food, etc. Whatever I do get there is quality and tasty. The staff is always personable, but after three visits with missing things, I can’t ignore that. It’s also not the kind of coffee shop I would stay at for a long time meeting someone or working; it doesn’t have that comfortable vibe.
Love this coffee shop and love the owner. Great place and delicious coffee!

I love craft coffee and Wildroots has been continuously supplying some of the best coffee in CLT for years! The PSL is the best I’ve ever had! And if you are looking for something different, try the PSL Matcha!!
Very neat little spot. Coffee was great and the service friendly. Evergthing was ready very quickly. Would go back if in the area again.
Best coffee in Charlotte. We chose to sit down and enjoy our coffee and were able to choose from a variety of coffee cups to drink out of. Definitely coming back again
Two starts because the place is unbelievably cute! Unfortunately I didn’t make it 10 feet on the sidewalk before throwing away my latte. The quality of espresso was tragic
This coffee shop is super cute and had a great atmosphere. They have tables and these cute little cubby holes to relax in more private. The coffee was good and they have free wifi!

Undoubtedly, this coffee shop is a true hidden gem. Every flavor on their menu is exceptional, with my personal favorite being the Honey Cinnamon Latte. The owner and baristas create a friendly and welcoming atmosphere. Moreover, the shop’s adorable ambiance adds to the overall experience. An added convenience is that they validate your parking so you are able to enjoy your time there without any worries. For anyone seeking the best and most delightful coffee experience in Charlotte, Wildroots is the place to be.
The blackberry cobbler was as cool and refreshing as the vibe in this sixties seventies nostalgic lounge!

4.5! Very nice barista, and the drinks were good too. I preferred the Blackberry Cobbler latte to my girlfriend’s Strawberry Dream, but she enjoyed hers too. We didn’t get to have them in the adorable glasses which was unfortunate, but we’ll be back!

Just had the Honduran dark roast as a pour over and it was good. Just the fact that they know where the bean was from and what kind of roast it is means they have a passion for good coffee. Plus the barista is incredibly cute! I’ll be back!
Great coffee shop and immaculate retro vibes! Definitely worth stopping in for a lavender latte or cortado. They validate parking too!
This place is a vibe. The decor is 70's vintage and the coffee options are so flavorful and unique. Would 10/10 recommend to grab an iced or hot coffee from this place.
Very sweet people and great coffee! We loved the furniture, style, and atmosphere of the shop. Barista was kind and even gave us breakfast recommendations!

They have such yummy coffee and the owner and her team are so nice.  The customer service is amazing and the ambience is super chill and relaxing.  I always look forward to grabbing a coffee from here!

My husband and I love this place we always go right before 2pm everything about their coffee is perfect. We are Colombian so we know about quality coffee. Their Lavender syrup which is naturally made is top notch and the staff, owner and overall place is always on point and extremely nice! We are customers and we followed to the new location!
My latte was bitter and very overpriced.
Slow. 20 minutes for two coffees. I was the only customer in the shop
Awesome coffee!
Amazing coffee and a great atmosphere. Try the honey cinnamon. You won't regret it. This place is a whole vibe. Definitely making this a regular coffee spot to visit in Southend!

The coffee was very good but it was hard to even find the coffee shop because it’s hard to see from the outside and also having no bathroom isn’t cool at all for a place that literally sells something that’s a diuretic. A good place to just grab a coffee and go I guess.
Cool space but terribly pulled espresso and no restroom. How does a coffee shop not have a restroom?

It's a very cute and cozy coffee shop where I always feel welcomed. Baristas there would always greet me with a smile and would customize any drink to my liking. Great to have this option near work. The entrance is to the right of the Sweat Method. They close at 2:00 pm.

Extremely quaint and comfortable inside. Honey-cinnamon latte was delicious. Definitely a good little spot to grab a cup of coffee with friends.

Seating is a bit limited inside, but we had no problem getting a seat.

This place is wonderful. The coffee (and tea) are both perfectly made, each and every time. Walking in, the shop itself was so thoughtfully curated. Everything is so aesthetically pleasing! And don’t get me started on the owner, Jasmine, she’s so sweet. 100% would recomment!
Always a great visit. The oat milk iced cortado is so smooth, staff is friendly, and they serve local coffee!!!  Must try!
Iced oatmilk latte was good, but the highlight of my visit was the vegan blueberry lemon pop-tart! So delicious and not overly sweet👌🏼Cool area too.

What once was the cutest little coffee trailer is now the cutest little coffee shop in South End.

I give this place five stars, but if what the other reviewer said about no public restroom and no air conditioning is true, I would knock my rating down. (It was cold and rainy the day I went)
Wonderful coffee.  Wonderful owner.  Hard to beat it in Southend.

One of the best coffee shops I’ve visited. Locally owned and an absolutely beautiful atmosphere!! Payment was easy and the espresso was NOT BURNT! YAY!!
Great options for flavored lattes!
Kind service and great hot chocolate with several milk options. Will be back!
Delish iced latte, cute interior, and good convo with the owner! Excited to go back.
